"hundreds and hundreds of unique beers are listed for goose island, so of course all of them cant be back yard rye bourbon county or madame rose right? well, this one feels a bit corporate, like a reach to the perimeters of craft beer, rather than a beer for those at the center. i appreciate bringing new people on board, but they already have beer for that. this is a dumbed down american pale, pretty tasty actually in its hop profile, and very fresh, but there just isnt enough of it. its like the flavor is great but the part that makes it great is reduced or suppressed or just a flash rather than a presence. grassy and floral and summery are the hops, very mild bitterness, and an irrelevant grain base thats clean and simple without much structure. i know the purpose of this beer, and i can appreciate that, but i know they are capable of making better beer, so i have mixed feelings about this one. totally pleasant and definitely a league better than other beers that will share its contexts."
