"Gotta admit I like this one. It's a well balanced pale ale with all the attributes of a good balanced pale ale. Malt and hops are blended well with some biscuit, bread, and caramel malt mixed nicely with some crisp, bitter hops. I find this beer refreshing and tasty, even more refreshing in that it's not caving to the new-fangled trend of ridiculously over-hopping everything and then rating it really high because it's chock full of ridiculously inappropriate levels of hops. Good job Goose Island on making a pale ale that's a friggin' pale ale and not an IPA."
