"12 ounce bottle into pint glass, bottled on 2/25/2014. Pours fairly crystal clear deep golden color with a 1-2 finger dense off white head with good retention, that reduces to a small cap that lingers. Nice soapy lacing clings on the glass, with a moderate amount of streaming carbonation. Aromas of lemon zest, tangerine, orange peel, grapefruit, floral, grass, light pine, wheat, biscuit, light caramel, and floral earthiness. Nice and pleasant aromas with good balance of bright citrus hops and pale malt notes; with solid strength. Taste of lemon zest, tangerine, grapefruit, orange peel, floral, grass, light pine, wheat, biscuit, light caramel, and floral earthiness. Fair amount of earthy floral/grassy bitterness on the finish; with lingering notes of lemon zest, tangerine, grapefruit, orange peel, floral, grass, biscuit, wheat, light caramel, and floral earthiness on the finish. Nice balance and complexity of citrus hops and pale malt sweetness; with a good malt/bitterness balance and no cloying flavors after the finish. Medium carbonation and body; with a lightly creamy, smooth, and fairly crisp/bready mouthfeel that is nice. Alcohol is well hidden with minimal warming present after the finish. Overall this is a nice pale ale style. Good balance and complexity of citrus hops and pale malt sweetness; and very smooth to drink. A nicely enjoyable offering."
